HEADWORD: Pragmatism
<hw>Prag"ma*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being pragmatic; in literature, the pragmatic, or
philosophical, method.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The narration of this apparently trifling circumstance belongs to
the <qex>pragmatism</qex> of the history.</q> <rj><qau>A.
Murphy.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pragmatist</ent>⟦br⟧
